<subSubSection id="C3266509FFDCFFB2EBA2FE70FD89FA4C" pageId="9" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B833682FFDCFFB2EBA2FE70FBCDFE4B" blockId="9.[151,1436,151,464]" pageId="9">
<emphasis id="B948EA90FFDCFFB2EBA2FE70FEC3FE36" bold="true" box="[199,345,404,429]" pageId="9">Description.</emphasis>
In addition to the genus characters, species is noticeably smaller in size. Stridulum on FW with 22–29 numbers of teeth (n=2). Basitarsomere III with 4–5 inner and 6–7 outer spines.
</paragraph>
